-body-sm ds2-5-body-link" data-author-id="431142" href="https://unimelb.academia.edu/SuneelJethani">Suneel Jethani</a></div><p class="ds2-5-body-sm ds-related-work--abstract hide-on-large">Hi everyone, my name is Suneel Jethani I&#39;m based at the University of Melbourne in the Media and Communications Program. In this session about representation and mediation, unlike Rachel (Kent) and Donell (Holloway) who&#39;ve presented empirical studies, my paper is going to be a little looser and my focus is more to do with methodological approaches to the study of self-tracking. I&#39;m justifying this looseness in two ways. The first is because of jetlag. The type of jetlag that only an Australian in Europe can lay claim to. But the second and more relevant reason is that much of the thinking that guides this talk comes from the end stages of writing my PhD and two reflections on this process in particular. The first is that given I did my doctoral studies part time my research as been &#39;active&#39; over a longer period of time and that&#39;s seen many developments in the field and this means that the novelty factor has faded (for many of those engaging in self-tracking practices and from my perspective as a researcher). The second is that through the long process of researching and writing a PhD one tends to amass many documents, examples, media and other paratextual objects that support the body of work that becomes a PhD but aren&#39;t fully explored and acknowledged in the process of writing the thesis. So in this talk, I&#39;m going to try and deal with these two issues by formulating ways to critique the seeming novelty of self-tracking technologies when they present in certain contexts of everyday life as new, unprecedented and more often than not, unproblematic construction of self-tracking technology in research; and then look at ways that documentation as an outcome (and/or byproduct) of research can be put to good use in reframing self-tracking and generating the requisite critical distance that advances our research and keeps our critical perspective on things malleable and responsive to change.</p><div class="ds-related-work--ctas"><a class="ds2-5-text-link ds2-5-text-link--inline js-tc-loswp--wsj-grid-card-download-pdf-modal js-login-button--004b42fd"><span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">download</span><span class="ds2-5-text-link__content">Download free PDF</span></a><script>document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
